5 Whereas transparency, accessibility and meaningful participation of self-advocates throughout
6 all stages of policy development are essential to advancing equity and ensuring that decisions reflect
7 the lived experiences of individuals who rely on home and community-based services; and
8 Whereas taxpayers and the State of Oregon have a shared interest in the efficient use of public
