16 DEFINITIONS
17
18 SECTION 1. Definitions. As used in sections 1 to 13 of this 2026 Act:
19 (1) “Attendant care services” has the meaning given that term in ORS 427.191.
20 (2) “Developmental disability child foster home” has the meaning given that term in ORS
21 443.830.
22 (3)(a) “Direct care staff” means employees of a residential care facility, a residential
23 training facility or a residential training home whose primary responsibilities are to provide
24 personal care services to residents, including but not limited to:
25 (A) Administering medications;
26 (B) Coordinating resident-focused activities;
27 (C) Supervising and supporting residents;
28 (D) Supporting activities of daily living, including but not limited to bathing, dressing,
29 eating and transferring; and
30 (E) Serving but not preparing meals.
31 (b) “Direct care staff” does not include management-level staff, including nurses, physi-
32 cians and administrative staff.
33 (4) “Domiciliary care facilities” has the meaning given that term in ORS 443.205.
34 (5) “Employer organization” means a nonprofit trade association whose membership is
35 composed of or includes entities that employ workers of the home and community-based
36 services workforce in this state.
37 (6)(a) “Home and community-based services workforce” includes the following workers
38 who provide long-term care services and supports:
39 (A) A home care worker, as defined in ORS 410.600;
40 (B) A personal support worker, as defined in ORS 410.600;
41 (C) A personal care attendant;
42 (D) A direct support professional, as defined in ORS 427.191;
43 (E) An individual providing in-home care services as an employee of or under an ar-
44 rangement or contract with an in-home care agency, as defined in ORS 443.305;
45 (F) An individual providing attendant care services or personal care services as an em-
[2]

SB 1505
1 ployee of an organization that provides:
2 (i) Agency with choice services, as defined in ORS 427.181; or
3 (ii) Agency with choice services, as defined in ORS 443.360; and
4 (G) Direct care staff.
5 (b) “Home and community-based services workforce” does not include:
6 (A) A private pay home care worker, as defined in ORS 410.600.
7 (B) Management-level staff, including nurses, physicians and administrative staff.
8 (7) “In-home care services” has the meaning given that term in ORS 443.305.
9 (8) “Labor organization” has the meaning given that term in ORS 663.005.
10 (9) “Personal care attendant” means an individual who:
11 (a) Provides in-home care services to a person with a behavioral health condition or dis-
12 ability; and
13 (b) Meets the eligibility requirements established by rule by the Oregon Health Authority
14 in order to receive Medicaid reimbursement for such services.
15 (10) “Public hearing” means an open hearing conducted in accordance with the require-
16 ments for a public meeting under ORS 192.610 to 192.705.
17 (11) “Residential care facility” means a residential care facility, as defined in ORS 443.400,
18 with a memory care endorsement under ORS 443.886 and an assisted living facility.
19 (12) “Residential training facility” and “residential training home” have the meanings
20 given those terms in ORS 443.400.
21 (13) “Supported living services” means services that provide an individual with an intel-
22 lectual or developmental disability the ability to live in the community where the individual
23 wants, with whom the individuals wants, for as long as the individual desires.
