25 HOME AND COMMUNITY-BASED SERVICES
26 WORKFORCE STANDARDS BOARD
27
28 SECTION 2. Establishment; members; term; vacancies. (1) There is established the Home
29 and Community-Based Services Workforce Standards Board within the Department of Con-
30 sumer and Business Services. The purposes of the board are to:
31 (a) Strengthen and maintain a sufficient supply of a skilled home and community-based
32 services workforce by:
33 (A) Examining factors that may present challenges to recruiting and retaining workers,
34 including but not limited to compensation, work schedules and other working conditions; and
35 (B) Addressing barriers that may impact the sustainability of the workforce including
36 affordability, access, quality and satisfaction regarding home and community-based services;
37 and
38 (b) Make recommendations to revise the minimum workforce standards established by
39 the board under section 6 of this 2026 Act and adopt new standards, as needed, to improve
40 the working conditions of the home and community-based services workforce.
41 (2) The board shall consist of 11 members appointed as follows:
42 (a) Three members appointed by the Governor who represent the home and community-
43 based services workforce or labor organizations;
44 (b) Three members appointed by the Governor who represent employers of individuals
45 of the home and community-based services workforce or employer organizations;
[3]

