1 (c) Two members appointed by the Governor who receive services provided by the home
2 and community-based services workforce;
3 (d) One member appointed by the Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries
4 who represents the bureau;
5 (e) One member appointed by the Governor who represents the Department of Human
6 Services; and
7 (f) One member appointed by the Governor who represents the Oregon Health Authority.
8 (3) The appointments of the Governor under subsection (2)(a) to (c) of this section:
9 (a) Shall be subject to confirmation by the Senate in the manner provided by ORS 171.562
10 and 171.565.
11 (b) Must be individuals who, collectively, have current knowledge and experience in the
12 following home and community-based services or care settings:
13 (A) In-home care services;
14 (B) Attendant care services;
15 (C) Supported living services;
16 (D) Residential care facilities;
17 (E) Residential training facilities or residential training homes;
