1 based services workforce;
2 (B) Industry profitability and economic data that includes:
3 (i) Total reimbursement spending within the home and community-based services indus-
4 try;
5 (ii) The distribution of reimbursement spending among direct care labor costs, adminis-
6 trative and overhead costs and net income;
7 (iii) Average operating margins weighted by total revenue or service hours delivered; and
8 (iv) Disaggregation of the data described under this subparagraph by entity type of the
9 providers of home and community-based services;
10 (C) Testimony from current and former workers from the home and community-based
11 services workforce, labor organizations, employers and other interested stakeholders, in-
