32 proposed by the board do not conflict with any rule or standard established by the commis-
33 sion pursuant to Article XV, section 11, of the Oregon Constitution, or ORS 410.595 to
34 410.625.
35 (e) Consult with individuals receiving home and community-based services, including
36 self-advocates from diverse disability and aging communities, to ensure that the proposed
37 minimum standards relating to curriculum and criteria described under subsection (2)(b) of
38 this section:
39 (A) Reflect and reinforce the values of self-determination, independence and individual
40 choice for individuals receiving home and community-based services;
41 (B) Incorporate educational content that is designed or delivered by individuals receiving
42 home and community-based services or self-advocacy organizations representing such indi-
43 viduals; and
44 (C) Address training and competency needs identified by individuals receiving home and
45 community-based services, including barriers that limit access to high-quality services and
