27 unless such information is exempt from public disclosure under federal or state law.
28 (8) Rules establishing minimum standards under this section shall be adopted by the
29 board in accordance with applicable provisions of ORS chapter 183.
30 SECTION 7. Comprehensive review. (1) At least once every four years, the Home and
31 Community-Based Services Workforce Standards Board shall conduct a comprehensive re-
32 view of the minimum standards previously adopted by the board to determine whether the
33 standards have continuing applicability or whether the board should adopt new standards or
34 revise the existing standards.
35 (2)(a) As part of the review, the board shall conduct a labor market analysis of the
36 working conditions for the home and community-based services workforce that examines
37 factors that may include, but need not be limited to:
38 (A) Supply and demand estimates and projections for such workers;
39 (B) Education, training and skill requirements;
40 (C) Compensation rates for the home and community-based services workforce;
41 (D) Industry profits; and
42 (E) Professional development and training opportunities.
43 (b) In conducting the labor market analysis, the board shall consider whether and to
44 what extent the board’s minimum standards regarding compensation rates for paying work-
45 ers in the home and community-based services workforce should be adjusted relative to the
[7]

