10 (A) For statutory changes;
11 (B) For revisions to amounts appropriated to the board, if any; and
12 (C) For proposed adjustments to Medicaid reimbursement rates to ensure that such rates
13 directly correspond to the board’s minimum standards for compensation rates paid to the
14 home and community-based services workforce.
15 (b) A copy of the budget documents of the board showing:
16 (A) The Medicaid reimbursement rates for the home and community-based services
17 workforce; and
18 (B) Statements showing aggregate data regarding compensation paid and benefits pro-
19 vided to the home and community-based services workforce.
20 (c) A description of the public hearing process used to inform the minimum standards
21 established by the board.
22 (d) A description of the current minimum standards established by the board and re-
23 commended changes to the standards, along with any supporting documentation for the
24 proposed changes.
25 (e) The number and types of complaints or civil actions filed alleging a violation of any
26 of the standards established by the board, if any.
27 (f) A summary of all other actions taken during the prior biennium in the performance
28 of the board’s statutory responsibilities that is adequate to allow evaluation of the board’s
29 performance.
