13 SECTION 14. ORS 443.517 is amended to read:
14 443.517. (1) The Department of Human Services shall maintain an online [home or community-
15 based services caregiver] registry that is accessible to the public and that lists home or
16 community-based services caregivers and workers. The information to be displayed on the reg-
17 istry for each caregiver and worker, respectively, shall be limited to the:
18 (a) Name of the caregiver or worker;
19 (b) County and, if applicable, city where the caregiver or worker resides;
20 (c)(A) Certification status of the caregiver under ORS 443.515 and any endorsements earned by
21 the caregiver; [and] or
22 (B) Certification status of the worker and any endorsements earned by the worker, if
23 applicable; and
24 (d) Criminal records check status of the caregiver or worker.
25 (2) The registry shall contain links to:
26 (a) Sites that explain the training requirements for the certification of each type of home or
27 community-based services caregiver described in ORS 443.515 (1)(b); and
28 (b) The home care registry, as defined in ORS 410.600, for members of the public to find home
29 care workers.
30 (3) The department shall create a process for a home or community-based services caregiver or
31 worker to request to be excluded from the registry.
32 (4) The department shall prominently display a notice on the registry that states that:
33 (a) Home or community-based services caregivers and workers may choose not to be listed on
34 the registry; and
35 (b) The registry is not an exclusive list of all home and community-based services caregivers
36 and workers that are qualified and trained in this state.
37 (5) The department may include on the registry disclaimers, user guidance and other resources
38 that the department deems appropriate to help users of the registry.
39 (6) This section does not prohibit the department from requesting and collecting from home or
40 community-based services caregivers and workers information in addition to the information that
41 must be displayed on the registry under subsection (1) of this section.
42 (7) As used in this section, “worker” means an individual from the home and
43 community-based services workforce, as defined in section 1 of this 2026 Act.
