17 (a) Apply to:
18 (A) Hearings under ORS 197.797, 215.402 to 215.438 and 215.700 to 215.780 regardless of whether
19 a governing body or governing body’s designee, including a hearings officer, conducts the hearing;
20 and
21 (B) Public hearings under section 5 of this 2026 Act; and
22 (b) Do not apply to contested case hearings under ORS chapter 183.
23 SECTION 16. (1)(a) The Home and Community-Based Services Workforce Standards
24 Board shall consider the information related to prevailing labor market conditions described
25 under section 6 (3) of this 2026 Act no later than September 30, 2028.
26 (b) The board shall adopt rules establishing the initial minimum standards under section
27 6 of this 2026 Act following completion of the initial market study described in paragraph (a)
28 of this subsection, but not sooner than March 1, 2029.
29 (2) If, as a result of a fiscal impact analysis conducted under section 6 (4) of this 2026
30 Act, the Bureau of Labor and Industries, the Department of Consumer and Business Ser-
31 vices, the Department of Human Services or the Oregon Health Authority determines that
32 a proposed minimum standard will require any increase to state funding levels or otherwise
33 result in an increase in the fiscal obligations of the state, the board shall report to the
34 Legislative Assembly and to the Governor the increase in funding needed to implement the
35 standard. The rule establishing the standard may not take effect until the regular legislative
36 session next following provided that an appropriation has been made for purposes of imple-
37 menting and enforcing the standard, in the regular legislative session next following.
38 SECTION 17. The unit and section captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for
39 the convenience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or
40 express any legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
